briefdescription.para: Populates the master grid with data from the MySQL database.

detaileddescription.para: This function establishes a connection to the MySQL database and retrieves all records from the "lk1" table, ordered by the "cat" column. It then clears the current contents of the master grid and appends rows to match the number of records fetched from the database. The grid cells are populated with the data retrieved from the database.

simplesect.para: This function assumes that the MySQL connection object conn and the master grid object masterGrid are properly initialized.
If the database connection fails, the function will return immediately and the grid will not be populated.

briefdescription.para: Loads detailed data for a specific ID and populates a grid with the retrieved information.

detaileddescription.para: This method queries the database to retrieve data from the lk2 table where the idlk1 matches the provided ID. The result set is then used to populate a grid, clearing any existing rows and adding new rows as necessary.

idlk1
The ID used to filter the lk2 table in the query.
Steps:
Create a new query using the database connection.
Execute the query to select idlk2, lkn, lnk, and ddes columns from the lk2 table where idlk1 matches the input.
Clear the existing grid and delete any rows if present.
Append rows to the grid equal to the number of results returned by the query.
Populate the grid cells with the data from the query result set.
Clear the result set after processing.
Handles the event when a cell in the master grid is clicked.

event
The wxGridEvent object that contains event information.
Retrieves the row index of the clicked cell, extracts the value from the first column of that row, converts it to a long integer, and then loads the detailed data associated with the converted value.

briefdescription.para: Event handler for cell clicks in a wxGrid. OnMasterGridCellClick This function is triggered when a cell in the wxGrid is clicked. It retrieves the value of the clicked cell. If the value starts with "http", it attempts to open the URL in the default browser.

parameterdescription.para: Reference to the wxGridEvent triggered by the cell click.

detaileddescription.para: This function is triggered when the user selects the "Quit" option in the menu. It closes the application window.

parameterdescription.para: The wxCommandEvent object containing event details.
